  {"a":"aphelios_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Skill","Skill","Zeri","Aphelios","Skill","Aphelios","Aphelios"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zeri's level 3 spike is her mobility: with Q spam, W (Ultrashock Laser) poke and E (Spark Surge) dashes over walls she can hit-and-run and dodge your Calibrum poke, making it hard to pin her for a clean trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Zeri R (Lightning Crash) is a scaling teamfight steroid, not a lane execute, so level 6 is an even skill check; you can still answer a greedy step-up with your gun rotation and ult burst if she overstays."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike first and harder: your completed item plus a strong gun pairing (Infernum waveclear or Calibrum range) out-damages a Zeri who needs multiple items and stacks before her R steroid snowballs."},{"when":"Late","text":"Zeri scales dangerously, but your raw DPS with rotating guns and ult holds up if you deny her early; land Gravitum roots to catch her mid-dash and don't let her kite you with E over walls."}],"wants":{"you":["Land Calibrum marks and Gravitum slows to pin her mobility","Punish her weak early autos before she has items","Spike first with your one-item gun rotation"],"foe":["Kite with Q spam and E dashes to dodge your poke","Reach 2-3 items so Lightning Crash snowballs","Poke you down with Ultrashock Laser from range"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are an even skill lane; Zeri's autos are weak and short but her range and W poke keep it neutral, so farm cleanly and trade only when her Q is on cooldown.","mid":"At level 3 her mobility spike lets her hit-and-run and dodge your poke, but by levels 4-5 you retake control since your sustained gun damage beats her item-hungry early game and level 6 stays an even skill check.","late":"From your first item you spike first and can out-DPS her before her R steroid scales; keep landing Gravitum roots to punish her dashes and win the tempo before she comes fully online.","whys":["Level 1 is an even skill lane with weak Zeri autos and neutral trading.","Level 2 stays a skill check as neither side has a committal spike.","At level 3 Zeri's Q-W-E mobility lets her kite and dodge your poke, favoring her.","By levels 4-5 your sustained gun damage retakes control over her item-hungry kit.","Level 6 Lightning Crash is a scaling steroid, not a lane execute, so it's even.","At one item you spike first and harder than an item-dependent Zeri.","By two-plus items your gun rotation DPS holds up if you denied her early."]},
  {"a":"aphelios_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Aphelios","Skill","Aphelios","Aphelios"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs is a lane bully with Q (Bouncing Bomb) poke and W (Satchel Charge) to knock you back or blow up your wave, so play behind your minions, dodge the Q bounces, and don't let him shove-and-poke you off the CS uncontested."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ziggs R (Mega Inferno Bomb) is a long-range poke and objective tool, not a duel-ending nuke in lane, so level 6 is an even skill check; sidestep the telegraphed ult and answer with a gun rotation when he steps up to Q."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike first as a marksman: one completed item plus your Calibrum range lets you all-in past his Satchel disengage or out-siege him, since he has no reliable self-peel once W is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your sustained DPS out-duels his cooldown-based poke; if you or your support can close the gap past his W knockback, he folds, so kite around Satchel and punish the windows between his spells."}],"wants":{"you":["Stand behind minions to eat fewer Q bounces","Bait his W Satchel then all-in the cooldown window","Spike first with your one-item gun rotation and range"],"foe":["Poke you down with Bouncing Bomb from max range","Use Satchel Charge to knock you away and disengage","Shove the wave and zone you off CS with spell threat"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are an even skill lane on paper, but Ziggs's Q poke and waveclear pressure you, so respect his range, path behind minions to minimize bounce damage, and farm patiently rather than forcing bad trades.","mid":"By levels 4-5 you stabilize and start to win once you're in range, and level 6 stays an even skill check since his ult is a poke tool, not a lane execute; punish the cooldown windows after his W.","late":"From your first item onward you take over: your sustained gun-rotation DPS out-duels his burst-on-cooldown poke, and closing past his Satchel with support CC lets you all-in a squishy Ziggs who has no self-peel left.","whys":["Level 1 is an even skill lane with careful trading from both sides.","Level 2 stays a skill check as neither champion commits hard yet.","Level 3 remains even; his Q poke pressures but you can farm safely behind minions.","By levels 4-5 you stabilize and win exchanges once you close into gun range.","Level 6 is even since Mega Inferno Bomb is poke and objectives, not a lane execute.","At one item you spike first as a marksman and out-siege a self-peel-less Ziggs.","By two-plus items your sustained DPS out-duels his cooldown-based burst poke."]}
